<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<title>edvisor · partner program overview · 100.partners</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #f6f5f1;
    --ink: #0f0f0f;
    --muted: #8a8a85;
    --soft: #d9d8d2;
    --white: #ffffff;
    --accent: #c2410c;
    --green: #3f7a5e;
    --amber: #b88512;
    --rose:  #b23a5c;
    --indigo: #3a4a9e;
    --maxw: 820px;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; background: var(--bg); color: var(--ink); }
  body {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.6;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .wrap { max-width: var(--maxw); margin: 0 auto; padding: 56px 28px 120px; }

  /* Masthead */
  .mast {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
    padding: 14px 0; margin-bottom: 40px;
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
    font-size: 11px; text-transform: lowercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--muted); flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px;
  }
  .mast .logo {
    height: 48px; width: auto; display: block;
  }
  .mast .meta { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .mast .meta a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--soft); }
  .mast .meta a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
  a.inline {
    color: inherit; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--soft);
  }
  a.inline:hover { color: var(--accent); border-bottom-color: var(--accent); }
  .meta-line { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: 28px; }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    font-size: 26px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.35; letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink); max-width: 680px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .cursor {
    display: inline-block; width: 10px; height: 20px; background: var(--accent);
    vertical-align: -3px; animation: blink 1.1s steps(1) infinite; margin-left: 4px;
  }
  @keyframes blink { 50% { opacity: 0; } }

  /* Section header */
  .sec { margin: 48px 0 20px; }
  .sec-head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .sec-head svg { width: 18px; height: 18px; stroke: var(--ink); stroke-width: 1.25; fill: none; flex: none; }
  .sec-head .label {
    font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: lowercase; color: var(--muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .sec-head .label b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }
  .sec-head .rule { flex: 1; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--soft); }

  /* Copy */
  p { margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .lead { font-size: 13.5px; }
  .muted { color: var(--muted); }

  /* Stat tiles */
  .stats {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 10px; margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  .stat { border: 1px solid var(--ink); padding: 10px 12px; background: var(--bg); }
  .stat .k { font-size: 10px; color: var(--muted); text-transform: lowercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .stat .v { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; margin-top: 4px; }
  .stat .note { font-size: 10px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 3px; }

  /* Engine diagram */
  .engine {
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); padding: 20px; background: var(--white); margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .engine-row {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .engine-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .ch {
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); padding: 12px; background: var(--bg);
  }
  .ch .tag {
    display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: lowercase;
    padding: 2px 6px; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .ch h4 { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 6px; }
  .ch p { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.55; }
  .flow {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 14px;
    padding: 10px 0; font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .flow .step { border: 1px solid var(--ink); padding: 6px 10px; color: var(--ink); background: var(--bg); }
  .flow .step.active { background: var(--ink); color: var(--bg); }
  .flow .arrow { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .flow { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }

  /* P90 steps */
  .p90 { border: 1px solid var(--ink); background: var(--white); }
  .step-row {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 46px 150px 1fr; gap: 14px;
    padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--soft); align-items: baseline;
  }
  .step-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-row .n {
    font-size: 10px; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .step-row .t { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; }
  .step-row .d { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.55; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .step-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 4px; }
  }

  /* Cards / list */
  .cards {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .card { border: 1px solid var(--ink); padding: 16px; background: var(--white); }
  .card .topstripe { height: 3px; margin: -16px -16px 14px; }
  .card .eye {
    display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: lowercase;
    padding: 2px 6px; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .card h3 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.35; margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .card p { font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; }

  /* Stack table */
  .stack { border: 1px solid var(--ink); background: var(--white); }
  .stack .row {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 150px 1fr 120px; gap: 12px;
    padding: 10px 16px; border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--soft);
    align-items: baseline; font-size: 12px;
  }
  .stack .row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .stack .tool { font-weight: 600; }
  .stack .purpose { color: var(--muted); }
  .stack .use {
    font-size: 10px; text-transform: lowercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--accent);
    text-align: right;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .stack .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2px; }
    .stack .use { text-align: left; }
  }

  /* Terms box */
  .terms {
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); padding: 20px; background: var(--bg);
  }
  .terms h3 {
    font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 14px;
    display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 10px;
  }
  .terms h3 .price { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); }
  .terms h3 .per { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .terms .bullets { font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.8; }
  .terms .bullets div { display: flex; gap: 10px; align-items: baseline; }
  .terms .bullets .b { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }

  /* Next steps */
  .next {
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); padding: 18px 20px; background: var(--white);
  }
  .next ol { margin: 0; padding-left: 22px; font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.8; }
  .next ol li { padding-left: 4px; }
  .next ol li::marker { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }

  /* Pills */
  .pill {
    display: inline-block; font-size: 10px; padding: 2px 8px; border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent); margin-right: 6px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  /* Callout / thesis */
  .callout {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); padding: 6px 0 6px 14px;
    font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--ink); margin: 6px 0 18px;
  }

  /* Footer */
  footer {
    margin-top: 56px; padding-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px;
    font-size: 10px; color: var(--muted); text-transform: lowercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">

  <!-- ========== MASTHEAD ========== -->
  <div class="mast">
    <img class="logo" alt="100.partners" src="data:image/avif;base64," />
    <span class="meta"><a href="https://edvisor.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">edvisor</a> · nicholas · apr 17, 2026</span>
  </div>

  <div class="meta-line">// recap of our conversation · next steps inside · confidential</div>

  <!-- ========== HERO ========== -->
  <h1 class="hero">turn edvisor's network into a distribution engine.<span class="cursor"></span></h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">
    <a class="inline" href="https://edvisor.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">edvisor</a> is
    already the recruiting platform for international education. the job now is to turn your
    3,000-strong customer list into a formal partner channel, pair it with biweekly webinars,
    create an outbound engine, and make your sales team's calendars overflow with demos.
  </p>

  <!-- ========== SNAPSHOT ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="12" rx="0"/><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/><circle cx="17" cy="14" r="1.5"/></svg>
      <div class="label">[<b>snapshot</b>] the numbers we discussed</div>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="stats">
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">customer list</div><div class="v">3,000</div><div class="note">schools + agencies</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">conservative take rate</div><div class="v">10%+</div><div class="note">proven baseline</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">day-one partner count</div><div class="v">300</div><div class="note">possibly higher</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">sales seats to fill</div><div class="v">3</div><div class="note">americas · emea · apac</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">demo target</div><div class="v">~300 / mo</div><div class="note">5 per rep per day</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">current utilization</div><div class="v">~10%</div><div class="note">calendars wide open</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">engagement</div><div class="v">biweekly</div><div class="note">webinars on 1st + 15th</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="k">sprint length</div><div class="v">90 days</div><div class="note">design to launched</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ========== OPPORTUNITY ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1.5" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
      <div class="label">[<b>opportunity</b>] where the growth is next</div>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">
      edvisor has earned meaningful share across north and south america. the east is the next
      front: asia, emea, and apac. agents in nepal, turkey, vietnam, and across southeast asia
      want what you've built, and edvisor's neutrality as a platform makes you the obvious home.
      partners give you reach into markets outbound can't cold-pitch its way into.
    </p>
    <div class="callout">
      thesis. build an orchestrated go-to-market motion that leverages a formal partner channel,
      a biweekly value-led webinar as the nurturing engine, and a sniper-esque outbound layer
      that's tight, deeply personalized, and triggered on real signal across targeted eastern
      markets. partners create reach, the webinar warms, signal-based outbound surgically pulls
      the right accounts in, and every channel converges on one outcome: filled sales calendars.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ========== THE ENGINE ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="14" rx="0"/><line x1="3" y1="9" x2="21" y2="9"/><circle cx="7" cy="6.5" r="0.5" fill="currentColor"/><circle cx="10" cy="6.5" r="0.5" fill="currentColor"/><line x1="7" y1="13" x2="17" y2="13"/><line x1="7" y1="15.5" x2="14" y2="15.5"/></svg>
      <div class="label">[<b>engine</b>] three channels, one outcome</div>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="engine">
      <div class="engine-row">
        <div class="ch">
          <span class="tag" style="background:var(--accent);">partners</span>
          <h4>referrals</h4>
          <p>300+ partners push leads into the webinar and into direct demos. commission on sales, flat bounty on qualified demos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ch">
          <span class="tag" style="background:var(--indigo);">webinars</span>
          <h4>biweekly, value-led</h4>
          <p>sales director hosts. every two weeks. industry data, trends by market. a reason for partners and outbound to point.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ch">
          <span class="tag" style="background:var(--green);">outbound</span>
          <h4>email to non-clients</h4>
          <p>10 domains × 3 inboxes, warmed and running through instantly. pointed at the webinar, not the demo. value-first invite.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow">
        <div class="step">3 channels</div>
        <span class="arrow">→</span>
        <div class="step">webinar</div>
        <span class="arrow">→</span>
        <div class="step">demo</div>
        <span class="arrow">→</span>
        <div class="step active">closed</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="muted" style="font-size: 11.5px;">
      // why this funnel works. partners and outbound both have a reason to act because there's
      always a webinar coming up. the webinar does the warming. the demo does the closing. you
      stop chasing and start filtering. all incentives are aligned to drive demos.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ========== P90 ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="4,12 10,18 20,6"/></svg>
      <div class="label">[<b>p90</b>] installing the p90 system · 7 stages</div>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="p90">
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="n">01 · design</div>
        <div class="t">partner economics</div>
        <div class="d">
          commission structure, tier logic (silver → gold), partner-type splits (schools vs agencies),
          free-weeks reward model, optional subscription discount, one-layer sub-referral for multi-seat partners like ilac.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="n">02 · foundation</div>
        <div class="t">tech stack + infra</div>
        <div class="d">
          dub embedded in-app (one line of code, every customer gets a partner dashboard on login),
          cal.com for demos (native dub sync), attio for pipeline, instantly + 10 warmed domains × 3 inboxes for outbound.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="n">03 · recruit</div>
        <div class="t">inside-out launch</div>
        <div class="d">
          invite all 3,000 existing customers into the program first. cleanest recruit channel you'll ever have.
          parallel outbound prospecting for net-new partner targets across the east.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="n">04 · activate</div>
        <div class="t">first promotion</div>
        <div class="d">
          every two weeks, a fresh webinar creates a new "reason to share." partner kit ships with swipe copy,
          co-branded landing pages for top partners, and first-touch automation from customer → active partner.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="n">05 · nurture</div>
        <div class="t">automated biweekly newsletter</div>
        <div class="d">
          1st + 15th of every month. best practices, leaderboard, top earner spotlight, next webinar.
          running in the background so the community team can own 1:1 relationships, not comms.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="n">06 · collab</div>
        <div class="t">bespoke partner moves</div>
        <div class="d">
          big-audience partners get joint webinars, guest blog posts, and co-branded landing pages.
          your service partners (insurance, payments, accommodation) plug in at conferences and physical events.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="n">07 · analyze</div>
        <div class="t">claude + dub mcp</div>
        <div class="d">
          scheduled claude jobs pull dub weekly, surface top 10 / bottom 10, flag dormant partners,
          push a dashboard into your watchtower. the program optimizes on a loop, not a quarterly review.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ========== ECONOMICS ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="6" width="18" height="12" rx="0"/><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/><circle cx="17" cy="14" r="1.5"/></svg>
      <div class="label">[<b>economics</b>] what we'll design together</div>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="topstripe" style="background:var(--green);"></div>
        <span class="eye" style="background:var(--green);">preferred · agency side</span>
        <h3>free weeks on advisor subscription</h3>
        <p>costs you nothing, gives the agent real value. scales without touching margin. works as a clean "bring one, get one" motion for the agency side.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="topstripe" style="background:var(--amber);"></div>
        <span class="eye" style="background:var(--amber);">commission · on saas</span>
        <h3>percentage on subscription · up to 12 months</h3>
        <p>sustainable base commission, not lifetime. tier bump extends duration. we'll run the full partner economics exercise against your real margins before locking numbers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="topstripe" style="background:var(--rose);"></div>
        <span class="eye" style="background:var(--rose);">tier uplift · on transactions</span>
        <h3>insurance + payments commission bump</h3>
        <p>referring partners jump to the highest bupa / allianz insurance tier for a window without hitting volume requirements. ties referral behavior directly to edvisor's transactional revenue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="topstripe" style="background:var(--indigo);"></div>
        <span class="eye" style="background:var(--indigo);">double-sided</span>
        <h3>partner-unique discount for new signups</h3>
        <p>only visible through a partner's link. creates a real "use my code" incentive without touching your main price page. optional, on top of free weeks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 14px;">
      <span class="pill">sub-referral</span>
      <span class="pill">tier system</span>
      <span class="pill">partner-type splits</span>
      <span class="pill">no lifetime commissions</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ========== TECH STACK ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="4" y="4" width="16" height="16"/><rect x="4" y="4" width="4" height="4" fill="currentColor"/><rect x="12" y="4" width="4" height="4" fill="currentColor"/><rect x="8" y="8" width="4" height="4" fill="currentColor"/><rect x="16" y="8" width="4" height="4" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
      <div class="label">[<b>stack</b>] what we wire up in foundation</div>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="stack">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="tool">dub</div>
        <div class="purpose">partner tracking, embedded dashboard, commission attribution, mcp for claude</div>
        <div class="use">core</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="tool">cal.com</div>
        <div class="purpose">demo booking, round-robin to 3 reps, native dub sync so referrals track cleanly to calls</div>
        <div class="use">demos</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="tool">attio</div>
        <div class="purpose">crm + pipeline, ai templates to summarize demo calls, sales workflows (hubspot replacement)</div>
        <div class="use">pipeline</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="tool">instantly</div>
        <div class="purpose">outbound sending, inbox rotation, reply routing into sales team inbox</div>
        <div class="use">outbound</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="tool">10 domains × 3 inboxes</div>
        <div class="purpose">sending infrastructure, warmed over ~2 weeks, protects your main domain</div>
        <div class="use">infra</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="tool">claude scheduled jobs</div>
        <div class="purpose">weekly program analysis, leaderboard generation, dormant partner flags, watchtower hookup</div>
        <div class="use">ops</div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="tool">claude managed agents</div>
        <div class="purpose">always-on agents handling partner triage, activation nudges, signal monitoring, and outbound personalization at scale</div>
        <div class="use">agents</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ========== COMMUNITY HOOK ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M4 4h12a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v12H8a4 4 0 0 1-4-4z"/><line x1="4" y1="8" x2="20" y2="8"/><line x1="12" y1="4" x2="12" y2="20"/></svg>
      <div class="label">[<b>community</b>] where the program lives after launch</div>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>
    <p>
      once the machine is running, the referral layer sits with edvisor's community team, not a new marketing hire.
      your per-market community managers (brazil, colombia, turkey, next up: asia) already have the 1:1
      relationships. they take over partner onboarding, activation nudges, and local events. the sales
      director keeps the webinars. the sales team keeps the demos. no marketing team required.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ========== TERMS ========== -->
  <div class="sec">
